1
00:00:18,625 --> 00:00:22,750
All events depicted are fictional. The names, occupations, and actions of the characters are created for entertainment purposes. Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:00:23,291 --> 00:00:25,291
We can’t go on together anymore, right?

3
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:27,458
Ja, can you tell me something?

4
00:00:27,875 --> 00:00:31,166
I have retinal degeneration.

5
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,208
There’s no permanent cure for it.

6
00:00:34,708 --> 00:00:37,291
Even if you go blind, I’ll be the image

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,583
that’s clearest to you.

8
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:44,875
I want you to be the producer for the series soundtrack.

9
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:47,666
I like you, Fern.

10
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:50,958
You’ve got some nerve.

11
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:52,083
Hey!

12
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:53,375
Theme, don’t do this to me!

13
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:54,791
Theme!

14
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:56,041
Theme!

15
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:57,541
Theme!

16
00:00:58,125 --> 00:00:59,375
Theme, stay with me, man.

17
00:00:59,583 --> 00:01:00,416
Theme!

18
00:01:25,291 --> 00:01:26,416
Can I ask you something?

19
00:01:27,166 --> 00:01:32,833
Why are you so obsessed with this artist?

20
00:01:36,416 --> 00:01:37,958
Can you help me write a song?

21
00:01:38,416 --> 00:01:39,833
How do you want me to do?

22
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:40,875
What should it be about?

23
00:01:41,416 --> 00:01:43,666
About someone we keep watching from afar,

24
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:47,458
hoping they keep succeeding,

25
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:50,458
supporting them from behind,

26
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:58,000
and how they make us want to live each day to the fullest.

27
00:02:07,541 --> 00:02:08,083
Hey.

28
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,125
Are you in love?

29
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:13,083
Wow… is this based on real life?

30
00:02:13,958 --> 00:02:14,750
I like you, Fern.

31
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,000
I really like you, Fern.

32
00:02:39,958 --> 00:02:42,041
If I could turn back time,

33
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:47,666
I’d want to apologize to you for that day.

34
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:54,916
I wanted to hear it from your own mouth.

35
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,250
But I couldn’t.

36
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:03,416
I just couldn’t.

37
00:03:10,375 --> 00:03:10,916
P’Ja…

38
00:03:10,916 --> 00:03:11,708
It’s okay.

39
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:18,666
I don’t know how to explain it, P’Ja.

40
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:23,875
Can you bring P’Theme back?

41
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,791
I can’t bring him back.

42
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:30,583
There are so many feelings, P’Ja.

43
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:40,250
I feel guilty.. I feel sorry and...I'm in so much pain.

44
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:43,750
It’s okay.

45
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,875
Don’t blame yourself, Fern.

46
00:03:54,166 --> 00:03:58,791
You did the right thing being honest with your feelings.

47
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:04,333
I believe Theme would feel the same way.

48
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,125
I know, P’Pie.

49
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:15,166
But I don’t feel any better at all.

50
00:04:17,666 --> 00:04:20,500
I just want P’Theme back.

51
00:04:21,958 --> 00:04:24,083
But it’s impossible now.

52
00:04:26,875 --> 00:04:33,666
I know, you’re hurting so much, Fern.
But if you keep crying and being unhappy…

53
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:39,375
He’d be really worried about you, If he saw you like this. 

54
00:04:39,791 --> 00:04:48,958
I believe one day we’ll be strong enough to get through this.

55
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,500
I understand, P’Ja.

56
00:04:57,291 --> 00:04:58,083
I understand.

57
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:15,833
Ja, Viva wants to schedule a meeting at the company.
They said there’s something big to discuss.

58
00:05:35,041 --> 00:05:37,875
I just happened to notice that you’re way too cute.

59
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:40,708
And if I were to walk up and tell you that I like you,

60
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:44,000
I’m just afraid it wouldn’t end well.

61
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:49,416
It’s probably too difficult for me to flirt with you,

62
00:05:49,416 --> 00:05:52,083
But my heart has already fallen for you completely.

63
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:55,416
So I can only ask for a little kindness.

64
00:05:55,916 --> 00:06:00,625
Please have mercy on me, Let me be the one to take care of you.

65
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:07,041
I’m completely weak when it comes to you, Just one smile and my heart overflows.

66
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:12,166
Please have mercy on someone ordinary like me.

67
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:18,375
Let me be the one in the heart of someone like you.

68
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:22,250
Can I be the one? Can I be the one?

69
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,875
Can I be the one? Please let me be the one.

70
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:29,750
Let me be the one living in your heart.

71
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:34,750
It’s probably too difficult for me to flirt with you,

72
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:37,250
But my heart has already fallen for you completely.

73
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:40,583
So I can only ask for a little kindness.

74
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:46,250
Please have mercy on someone ordinary like me.

75
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:52,458
Let me be the one in the heart of someone like you.

76
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:57,958
Let me be the one in your heart —

77
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:04,333
if your heart still has some space for me.

78
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:07,416
“A star may fall, yet its love remains.”

79
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:23,333
P’Jack, do you know what this meeting is about?

80
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,375
I got called in urgently too.

81
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:26,500
You don’t know?

82
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:32,041
Uh, boss… aren’t you going to sit?

83
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:36,333
I’m not sitting today, because I’m not the one leading this meeting.

84
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:38,833
And I’m not the one who called everyone here today either.

85
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:40,666
Huh?

86
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,166
Then who is it?

87
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,791
The one who called this meeting today is..

88
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:05,666
It's me.

89
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:08,750
What?!

90
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:11,666
What is this?

91
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:12,750
Keng!

92
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:13,875
Why are you standing there?

93
00:08:14,375 --> 00:08:15,750
That’s not a place for a kid.

94
00:08:16,041 --> 00:08:17,666
Yeah, come here!

95
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:22,375
Everyone, this is Keng Korawit Phakornsap.

96
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:27,708
Chief Marketing Officer and one of Viva Entertainment’s top executive board members.

97
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,583
And he’s the one who called everyone here today.

98
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,125
What?

99
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:33,750
Wait…

100
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:37,250
Keng is with Viva?

101
00:08:37,583 --> 00:08:39,333
That last name… Phakornsap.

102
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:42,583
Actually, I’m Khun Korkarn’s son.

103
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:45,375
Huh?!

104
00:08:45,541 --> 00:08:46,666
Her son?

105
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:55,541
P’Ja, I have to apologize to everyone for not telling you the truth.

106
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:59,166
I just wanted to get to know you all. I just wanted to perform Likay, P’Ja.

107
00:08:59,166 --> 00:08:59,958
Wait.

108
00:09:00,916 --> 00:09:06,166
You’re the chairman’s son, so why would you want to do Likay with us?

109
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,708
I just like Likay, that’s all, P’.

110
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:16,541
But that’s still not a reason for you to lie to us.

111
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:19,666
No matter who you are or where you come from,

112
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:22,250
if you truly love Likay,

113
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:23,833
you can be with us.

114
00:09:24,916 --> 00:09:25,583
Yeah.

115
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:27,208
I don’t like liars.

116
00:09:27,791 --> 00:09:29,833
I don’t want to talk to P’Keng anymore.

117
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:31,166
I'm mad at you.

118
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,708
Fern, don’t sulk at me.

119
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:34,458
Hear me out.

120
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:37,041
The reason I called everyone here today…

121
00:09:38,291 --> 00:09:40,791
is because there’s something I want to do for Theme, my friend.

122
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:45,708
Pie.

123
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:46,333
Yes?

124
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:49,291
Do you remember when we talked about dreams?

125
00:09:50,125 --> 00:09:51,666
What was Theme’s dream?

126
00:09:54,416 --> 00:09:55,333
Mm…

127
00:09:56,500 --> 00:10:04,166
Oh, Theme said he wanted to have his own concert at least once in his life.

128
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,750
That’s it. I want to make that concert happen for Theme.

129
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:12,083
And I’m going to call it “Forever Theme Concert.”

130
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:16,333
And Viva Entertainment will be the main partner.

131
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:20,916
And Sroi Saeng Suriya has to be the main act.

132
00:10:26,666 --> 00:10:28,041
Okay… I’ll stop being mad a little.

133
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,000
P’Ja, I want to do it.

134
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:43,458
Then let’s do a farewell concert for Theme.

135
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,375
Give it your all, Keng.

136
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,458
Thank you, P’Ja.

137
00:10:55,125 --> 00:10:56,041
Thank you, everyone.

138
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:22,541
Alright then. About the house you’re taking everyone on an outing to.
Just tell me what day you’re going.

139
00:11:22,541 --> 00:11:24,916
I’ll have someone clean it up in advance.

140
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,291
Yes.

141
00:11:27,666 --> 00:11:29,333
And about the budget

142
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:32,958
once everything’s agreed with all parties, come tell me.

143
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:34,041
No problem.

144
00:11:35,458 --> 00:11:36,250
Thank you.

145
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:39,333
But don’t forget what we agreed on.

146
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,666
This time, I won’t go easy on you.

147
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:53,916
Yes. Once this event is over, I’ll take over like you want.
